database--> data store bhayera bascha-- database bata data fetch garni frontend ma

database bata frontend ma data dekhauna API act as a server.

API- Application programming interface --(You can think of it as a common language that lets different software systems communicate smoothly, without needing to know how the other is built.)

RTK Query--> Api ko end point k ho- body ma kei cha ki chaina- query ma k pathauni... 


modules--> library/package --codes are already defined in modules-- they are a file that contains code that can be reused in other parts of our program.


thread--> smallest unit of process -- helps in handling multiple requests simultaneously..
Node.js usually use one main thread(has hidden workers behind the scenes) node.js runs your javascript code.

Server:- {kitchen of the restaurant}server is a computer that provides services or data tp other computers. when a client ask for informations it sends it. server stores or processes information..

to run or create a server-- express.js framework is used

node modules-- 3 types;
1) Built-in modules
2) Local modules
3) Third-party modules


//File System- asynchronous hunuparcha -- file system module is used to work with files and folders in Node.js
1) fs.readfile  => reads file
2) fs.writefile => writes (create)
3) fs.appendfile => updates a file
4) fs.unlink => deletes a file
5) fs.existsSync => checks if the file exists or not
6) fs.mkdir => make a folder
7) fs.rmdir => remove a folder
8) fs.rename('./oldpath', './newpath') =>rename a file or folder or you can also move a file to diff folder using rename 


listen kina garni ta? => server ma kei request ayo bhane listen garnu parcha tyo anusar ko response dina -- listen garda euta port number pani dinu parni huncha


Status:- 
200=> OK - Success
201=> Created
400=> Bad request
401=> Unauthorized
405 => Method not allowed 
500=> intenal server error
429=> too many request
409=> duplicate

Mongoose is a Node.js library... it helps to connect to MongoDB


Middleware:- request ra response ko bicha ma auni function -- middlewaee checks incoming data
middleware ko lagi app.use() method use garcha

MVC pattern - Model, View, Controller Pattern

Controller -  le response dina help garcha

View - react.js ma huncha

Model (IMP)- planning data ko -- eg: product ma title rakhni ki description rakhni ki tyo sabai decide garera product model banuni -- model is created using mongoose and it defines what our data looks like. so model is a MongoDB collection.
 model banauda schema define garnu parcha-- schema ma data ko structure define garnu parcha jastai data ma k k halnu parcha
schema bata model bancha ani tya bata interact garera add, delete,get, update etc garni




Params => this parameter comes after colon(:) but is seperated by slash(/) ..... it is a part of URL.-- params means parameters-- eg: we have a url http://localhost:5000/products/123
here params is 123


Query => this parameter comes after ? in the URL



