token response ma pauni ho(jwt token is being used here)
token paayesi local storage ma save garni



----------------------------------------------MONGODB-------------------------------------------------------------------
//for adding moongose / mongodb in node.js
//mongodb is a database which stores data.
//moongose is a node.js library-- which is used to work with MongoDB more easily. makes the code cleaner and safer and helps in creating schemas, models, validation



step-1   npm init-y   this creates a package.json file to manage project dependencies
(this npm init-y is used when starting a new node  or javascript project)
step-2   install mongoose   npm install mongoose
step-3   connect to MongoDB  in your main applcation(index.js) ma import mongoose and establish a connection to your MongoDB database----for this you gotta install mongoDb atlas app and tya add to cluster ma gayera afno mongodb connection string thapauni

step-4   define mongoose schemas (schemas mean structure)-- models folder create garera schema define garni 
const productSchema = new mooongose.schema({
title: {
    type, required, enum, default, unique
}
},{ timestamps: true });
const Product = mongoose.model('Product', productSchema);
export default Product;

step-5   perform CRUD(create, read, update, delete) operations -- use mongoose models in application logic like in routes, controllers, middleware to interact with MongoDB database


